Edge computing has gained significant traction in recent years due to the increasing demand for real-time data processing and the rise of connected devices. The global edge computing market is expected to witness substantial growth from 2021 to 2030. Factors driving this growth include the proliferation of Internet of Things (IoT) devices, the need for low-latency data processing, and the emergence of technologies such as 5G. Moreover, the adoption of edge computing solutions across various industries, such as manufacturing, healthcare, and transportation, is also contributing to market expansion.

